The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Nov. 8: Minister for heavy industries Santosh Mohan Dev said the government will decide on selling its 10.27 per cent residual stake in Maruti Udyog this month. A decision will be taken this month and implementation will be done next month, he said. He said a final note has been moved for the consideration of various ministries and coalition partners. 

 New Delhi, Nov. 8: Petroleum minister Murli Deora today said international crude prices would have to come down further and stabilise at lower levels before the government could think of reducing the prices of petrol and diesel.

 New Delhi, Nov. 8: Coca-Cola is investing about $250 million to consolidate its bottling operations in India. The fresh funds would be utilised by the companys bottling arm Hindustan Coca-Cola Beverages for a one-time buyout of excess capacities from its bottlers instead of paying them an assured sum over a period of time.

 New Delhi, Nov. 8: Gillette India will sell its office space near New Delhi from where it used to operate previously as part of its restructuring process.

 Bangalore, Nov. 8: Tata Coffee has entered into an agreement with the Ugandan government to set up a 3,600-tonne-per-annum plant in the country at an investment of Rs 70 crore.




